  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Preparing the enterprise to work with assets means assessing several key areas such as:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Governance&lt;/strong>: is the enterprise willing and able to establish the policies and decisions providing&#xD;
        the context for asset reuse within a reuse scope&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Process&lt;/strong>: where and when will the asset governance and asset-based development capability patterns&#xD;
        be inserted into existing processes&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Opportunity&lt;/strong>:what are the opportunities for assets within a reuse scope&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Aptitude&lt;/strong>: what is the ability and willingness of teams and individuals to work with assets&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Tools&lt;/strong>:what are the tools, repositories, and their configuration to support work with assets&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Governance&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Items to consider in this assessment include:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ol>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        What is the problem, or problems, the enterprise is trying to solve using assets?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Will the enterprise fund the activities of a governance board?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        To what level of management will the governance board report?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Who will approve and enforce the policies established by the governance board?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        How will the communities migrate to adopt the policies?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        How far along is the enterprise in defining the following: &amp;nbsp; &#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                access control to assets.&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                asset review and approval processes.&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                asset types.&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                asset versioning strategy.&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                classification schemas.&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                measurements and metrics.&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                policies.&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                repositories and their communities.&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ol>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Process&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Items to consider in this assessment include:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ol>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        What processes are candidates for updating with the asset capability patterns?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        What projects are candidates for applying the updated processes?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        What impacts to schedules and budgets will the processes updated with asset capability patterns require?&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Who will own the definition and refinement of the asset capability patterns for the reuse scope?&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        What enablement will be needed to bring teams up to speed on assets?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ol>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Opportunity and Aptitude&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    To assess for opportunity and aptitude the reuse assessment should be conducted. In this assessment the focus is on&#xD;
    understanding what opportunities are available for the creation and use of assets within a reuse scope:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ol>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Upon conducting the reuse assessment, what is the estimated size and number of assets?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Are there cultural issues which will impede asset adoption?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ol>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Tools&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    There are several kinds of tools for supporting asset-based development. The asset repository is a key tool; items to&#xD;
    consider in this assessment for the repository include:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ol>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        How does the enterprise plan on using the repository?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Given the estimates on number of assets, what is the expected growth in terms of numbers?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        In what format are current assets captured?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        What is the level of effort to migrate existing assets to the repository?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        How many users do you anticipate on the repository?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        How many groups or communities do you expect?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        What kinds of connections are required for the communities?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        What kinds of review processes are required for the communities?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        How will you manage authentication of users? LDAP?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        What kinds of roles and access control do you expect on the repository?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        When do assets expire? When will they be retired?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ol></mainDescription>
